Calculate the historical forecast error for a VAR out to a specified horizon

fe.Rd

Calculate the historical forecast error for a VAR out to a specified horizon

Usage

fe(var, horizon = 1)

Arguments

var

vars::VAR or svars object

horizon

number of steps out to calculate fe

Value

forecast error

Examples

x <- svars::USA
v <- vars::VAR(x, p = 2)
fe(v, 10)
